t the shadowy conspiracy of monastery monks using only his intelligence; which is considerable.","genre_ids":[18,53,9648],"popularity":3.3077,"vote_count":3251,"poster_path":"/d6dlbTBb3N7nXDz7tQslDJs2jgv.jpg","release_date":"1986-09-24","vote_average":7.492,"backdrop_path":"/v4d6PPfqHeUNSdcyBVQ2Xb8yBk0.jpg","original_title":"The Name of the Rose","original_language":"en"},{"id":947992,"adult":false,"title":"Zlaté rybičky","video":false,"overview":"","genre_ids":[18,80,10770],"popularity":1.3262,"vote_count":4,"poster_path":null,"release_date":"1979-05-19","vote_average":4,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Zlaté rybičky","original_language":"cs"},{"id":419272,"adult":false,"title":"Pony Girl","video":false,"overview":"Under the direction of a wealthy pervert, young women are being kidnapped, shipped off to a remote ranch and forced to submit and behave like horses by a whip-wielding dominatrix. This shot-on-video thriller with just R-rated nudity is noteworthy as one of the only non-porn films Traci Lords appeared in prior to the discovery of true age. She co-stars along with future Scream Queen Michelle Bauer.","genre_ids":[53],"popularity":1.9115,"vote_count":2,"poster_path":"/yFxJeOzr8TfDSfgVZtxOfcfyh0l.jpg","release_date":"1985-01-01","vote_average":6.5,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Pony Girl","original_language":"en"},{"id":419276,"adult":false,"title":"Pony Girl: At the Ranch","video":false,"overview":"Young women are being kidnapped by a rich sleazebag and his goons and are taken to a farm. At night they are forced to sleep on a barn floor. During the day, they are at the mercy of a sadistic dominatrix who dresses in leather outfits and forces them to behave like horses. This video uses footage from Pony Girl (1985) and Pony Girl Number Two (1985), with Traci Lords edited out of the proceedings despite the fact there's no X-rated material in the original tapes.","genre_ids":[53],"popularity":0.5908,"vote_count":3,"poster_path":"/q7AQ0VSd85S9fi8lkDW65yxcKBk.jpg","release_date":"1986-01-01","vote_average":7.7,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Pony Girl: At the Ranch","original_language":"en"},{"id":646,"adult":false,"title":"Dr. No","video":false,"overview":"Agent 007 battles mysterious Dr. No, a scientific genius bent on destroying the U.S. space program. As the countdown to disaster begins, Bond must go to Jamaica, where he encounters beautiful Honey Ryder, to confront a megalomaniacal villain in his massive island headquarters.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":7.2117,"vote_count":3954,"poster_path":"/f9HsemSsBEHN5eoMble1bj6fDxs.jpg","release_date":"1962-10-07","vote_average":6.99,"backdrop_path":"/ptcXbbxTyjHfEE4d4QocNP0YQct.jpg","original_title":"Dr. No","original_language":"en"},{"id":657,"adult":false,"title":"From Russia with Love","video":false,"overview":"Agent 007 is back in the second installment of the James Bond series, this time battling a secret crime organization known as SPECTRE. Russians Rosa Klebb and Kronsteen are out to snatch a decoding device known as the Lektor, using the ravishing Tatiana to lure Bond into helping them. Bond willingly travels to meet Tatiana in Istanbul, where he must rely on his wits to escape with his life in a series of deadly encounters with the enemy.","genre_ids":[28,53,12],"popularity":6.5294,"vote_count":3278,"poster_path":"/zx4V17FP8oclNvOpTgs2iCCtiYk.jpg","release_date":"1963-10-10","vote_average":7.065,"backdrop_path":"/8JMiQa0OqsCYvbNUrQIrMzwV7g2.jpg","original_title":"From Russia with Love","original_language":"en"},{"id":658,"adult":false,"title":"Goldfinger","video":false,"overview":"Special agent 007 comes face to face with one of the most notorious villains of all time, and now he must outwit and outgun the powerful tycoon to prevent him from cashing in on a devious scheme to raid Fort Knox -- and obliterate the world's economy.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":6.2145,"vote_count":3870,"poster_path":"/aKNFzaqQgPzsGXnsMc4kJH5hFIV.jpg","release_date":"1964-09-20","vote_average":7.355,"backdrop_path":"/f1Is9VLQZSRpeLMU7mIcj5aXclt.jpg","original_title":"Goldfinger","original_language":"en"},{"id":667,"adult":false,"title":"You Only Live Twice","video":false,"overview":"A mysterious spacecraft captures Russian and American space capsules and brings the two superpowers to the brink of war. James Bond investigates the case in Japan and comes face to face with his archenemy Blofeld.","genre_ids":[28,53,12],"popularity":7.1355,"vote_count":2402,"poster_path":"/fdRbvRcEXcf2rC4ghLFZzCWPSmB.jpg","release_date":"1967-06-13","vote_average":6.593,"backdrop_path":"/cpZAXIYA0lkZMpAt7d1MmH8ojNV.jpg","original_title":"You Only Live Twice","original_language":"en"},{"id":668,"adult":false,"title":"On Her Majesty's Secret Service","video":false,"overview":"With the help of Marc-Ange Draco, head of the Unione Corse crime syndicate, and Draco's troubled daughter Tracy, James Bond tracks his archnemesis, Ernst Stravro Blofeld, to a mountaintop retreat in the Swiss Alps, where he is training an army of beautiful, lethal women.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":5.3271,"vote_count":2077,"poster_path":"/m3KfbxvqaiAvRJ6MpguA3GuLdDQ.jpg","release_date":"1969-12-18","vote_average":6.562,"backdrop_path":"/58pMrmwwcKamJIdjUlinE6QX1Fs.jpg","original_title":"On Her Majesty's Secret Service","original_language":"en"},{"id":682,"adult":false,"title":"The Man with the Golden Gun","video":false,"overview":"Cool government operative James Bond searches for a stolen invention that can turn the sun's heat into a destructive weapon. He soon crosses paths with the menacing Francisco Scaramanga, a hitman so skilled he has a seven-figure working fee. Bond then joins forces with the swimsuit-clad Mary Goodnight, and together they track Scaramanga to a Thai tropical isle hideout where the killer-for-hire lures the slick spy into a deadly maze for a final duel.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":4.9709,"vote_count":2220,"poster_path":"/xVkbKwGnBVNQ122GN5bCTMyPbWz.jpg","release_date":"1974-12-04","vote_average":6.456,"backdrop_path":"/3tpNEbRahT8smy7RraaWa0xg9Gv.jpg","original_title":"The Man with the Golden Gun","original_language":"en"},{"id":691,"adult":false,"title":"The Spy Who Loved Me","video":false,"overview":"Russian and British submarines with nuclear missiles on board both vanish from sight without a trace. England and Russia both blame each other as James Bond tries to solve the riddle of the disappearing ships. But the KGB also has an agent on the case.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":5.5757,"vote_count":2165,"poster_path":"/3ZxHKFxMYvAko680DsRgAZKWcLi.jpg","release_date":"1977-07-07","vote_average":6.8,"backdrop_path":"/8lRdfsmJjUXQU3DMOOB3vVIhJxP.jpg","original_title":"The Spy Who Loved Me","original_language":"en"},{"id":694,"adult":false,"title":"The Shining","video":false,"overview":"Jack Torrance accepts a caretaker job at the Overlook Hotel, where he, along with his wife Wendy and their son Danny, must live isolated from the rest of the world for the winter. But they aren't prepared for the madness that lurks within.","genre_ids":[27,53],"popularity":14.883,"vote_count":18628,"poster_path":"/uAR0AWqhQL1hQa69UDEbb2rE5Wx.jpg","release_date":"1980-05-23","vote_average":8.2,"backdrop_path":"/mmd1HnuvAzFc4iuVJcnBrhDNEKr.jpg","original_title":"The Shining","original_language":"en"},{"id":698,"adult":false,"title":"Moonraker","video":false,"overview":"After Drax Industries' Moonraker space shuttle is hijacked, secret agent James Bond is assigned to investigate, traveling to California to meet the company's owner, the mysterious Hugo Drax. With the help of scientist Dr. Holly Goodhead, Bond soon uncovers Drax's nefarious plans for humanity, all the while fending off an old nemesis, Jaws, and venturing to Venice, Rio, the Amazon...and even outer space.","genre_ids":[28,12,53,878],"popularity":5.3553,"vote_count":2152,"poster_path":"/6LrJdXNmu5uHOVALZxVYd44Lva0.jpg","release_date":"1979-06-26","vote_average":6.181,"backdrop_path":"/mrDC5DLx2wljt4HZGwgkmqlzfcF.jpg","original_title":"Moonraker","original_language":"en"},{"id":750,"adult":false,"title":"Murder She Said","video":false,"overview":"Miss Marple believes she's seen a murder in a passing-by train, yet when the police find no evidence she decides to investigate it on her own.","genre_ids":[35,80,18,9648],"popularity":0.9755,"vote_count":229,"poster_path":"/tqnUJyeirufO0q29PoSPaCpB27E.jpg","release_date":"1961-09-26","vote_average":7.33,"backdrop_path":"/7LAV57poNxNHfDoMq3WslheohbX.jpg","original_title":"Murder She Said","original_language":"en"},{"id":751,"adult":false,"title":"Murder at the Gallop","video":false,"overview":"Miss Marple and Mr. Stringer are witnesses to the death by heart attack of elderly, rich Mr. Enderby. Yet they have their doubts about what happened. The police don't believe them, thus leading Miss Marple to yet again investigate by herself.","genre_ids":[35,80,18,9648,53],"popularity":0.6395,"vote_count":180,"poster_path":"/lCLJ6yutSJc8PkiazcEh8dB6Juh.jpg","release_date":"1963-05-09","vote_average":7.075,"backdrop_path":"/qUInTApfYSwiDYGY89lWqgWc0.jpg","original_title":"Murder at the Gallop","original_language":"en"},{"id":757,"adult":false,"title":"Murder Most Foul","video":false,"overview":"A murderer is brought to court and only Miss Marple is unconvinced of his innocence. Once again she begins her own investigation.","genre_ids":[35,80,18,9648,53],"popularity":1.0422,"vote_count":166,"poster_path":"/qTCKB5rxYzgdWUUH4UMgpRVH3GJ.jpg","release_date":"1964-03-01","vote_average":7.063,"backdrop_path":"/pTntob09b9616xtluRPO5Wl8Y3B.jpg","original_title":"Murder Most Foul","original_language":"en"},{"id":769,"adult":false,"title":"GoodFellas","video":false,"overview":"The true story of Henry Hill, a half-Irish, half-Sicilian Brooklyn kid who is adopted by neighbourhood gangsters at an early age and climbs the ranks of a Mafia family under the guidance of Jimmy Conway.","genr